---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import storyImg from "../assets/gallery/524639802_4104232946512149_2651185876716431935_n-682x1024.jpg";
---

<section id="story" class="section story">
  <div class="container-wide story__grid">
    <div class="story__copy reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Our Story</p>
      <h2 class="story__title script">Alyssa &amp; Nathan</h2>
      <p class="story__subtitle">~ Alyssa's POV ~</p>

      <h3 class="story__lede">It all started with pizza.</h3>

      <p>Well… sort of.</p>

      <p>
        In 2021, my mom worked at a local pizza shop and kept talking about this guy named
        Nathan — how smart, kind, and down-to-earth he was. She was convinced we'd hit it off
        and, naturally, I was skeptical.
      </p>

      <p>When I asked what he liked to do for fun, she said, "He plays video games."</p>

      <p>That was an instant nope from me.</p>

      <p>
        Fast forward a few weeks, and I started noticing him working the front desk at the gym
        I had just started going to. Eventually, I caved and asked him to make me a workout
        plan — even though I was a tri-sport athlete in high school, I had to act like I had
        no idea what I was doing just so he'd help me.
      </p>

      <p>
        But somehow, I stopped focusing on the workouts… and started focusing on how Nathan
        strutted around the gym like he owned the place (and looked dang good doing it).
      </p>

      <p>
        We eventually started hanging out. Then dating (after he asked me out while we were
        sitting on my brother's living room couch). And even though I was determined not to
        say it first, I ended up being the one to say "I love you" first.
      </p>

      <p>
        So, from pizza shop matchmaking to gym crushes and late nights binge-watching our
        favorite Netflix series (the "I love you" happened halfway through season two of
        <em>Breaking Bad</em>, by the way), we've built something real, steady, and full of
        love.
      </p>

      <p>
        Now, we can't wait to spend forever together — starting with a party surrounded by the
        people we love most.
      </p>

      <p class="story__sign script" aria-hidden="true">Alyssa &amp; Nathan</p>
    </div>

    <figure class="story__figure reveal">
      <Image
        src={storyImg}
        alt="Alyssa and Nathan"
        widths={[400, 600, 800, 1000]}
        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 90vw, 480px"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .story {
    background: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .story__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .story__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .story__copy { order: 1; }
  .story__figure { order: 2; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .story__figure { order: 1; }
    .story__copy { order: 2; }
  }

  .story__title {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5.5rem);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.25rem;
    color: var(--color-rose-deep);
  }
  .story__subtitle {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }
  .story__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .story__copy p {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.4vw, 1.125rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }
  .story__sign {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--color-rose-deep);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .story__figure {
    margin: 0;
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .story__figure {
      position: static;
      max-width: 26rem;
      margin-inline: auto;
    }
  }
  .story__figure :global(img) {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 2px;
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 0 var(--color-stone),
      0 30px 60px -30px rgba(40, 30, 25, 0.35);
  }
</style>
